verbose_text: Thus, it has been suggested that exercise, apart from inducing an overexpression of beta adrenergic receptors in immune cells [XREF_BIBR], causes a reduction in the expression of TLR receptors, the deregulation of cytokine production, the percentage of CD14+ CD16+ monocytes, and adipose tissue inflammation (by suppression of macrophage infiltration and switch from M1 to M2 phenotype).
